<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                </head>
                                <p>The Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_844">p.
                                        844</ref>, records that Roosevelt and Churchill conferred
                                    from 11 p.m. until midnight. No record of the discussion has
                                    been found. With reference to the meeting at 10 p.m. which
                                    preceded this conference, in which the Log states that
                                    Roosevelt, Hull, and Eden took part, see <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_930">p. 930</ref>, fn. 1.</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>